JC-Computation

Computation as a commons: open participation, universal verification, and deterministic outcomes.

The machine does not care who you are. It only cares whether the proof is valid.

Math is the governor. History is the source of truth. Computation is the constitution.

JC-Computation is a distributed quotient-rewriting engine over causal history space, implemented in Rust.

This software is founded on the principle that convergence should be a property of mathematics rather than authority. State is derived, histories are auditable, and identical causal knowledge produces identical outcomes.

No permission is required to inspect, verify, reproduce, extend, or redistribute this work. Participation is open to all. Verification is universal. Determinism is the mechanism through which independent actors arrive at shared truth.

The ideas, proofs, implementations, and derivative works enabled by this license remain subject only to the conditions stated above.



